The paper discusses an ontology-based question answering system, which falls under the categories of natural language processing (cs.CL), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), information retrieval (cs.IR), machine learning (cs.LG), and neural networks (cs.NE). The use of semantic web information and concept-matching techniques also suggests a focus on knowledge representation and reasoning (cs.AI).
